      • onEnterUnsubscribed

        public void onEnterUnsubscribed(UnsubscribeRequest request,
                                UnsubscribeReply reply)
        Description copied from interface: SubscriptionListener
        Called when a subscription enters the unsubscribed state. This is the initial state for the subscription state machine.

        A subscription enters this state in the following situations:

        • Subscription has been created and initialized with unsubscribed state.
        • Connection is dropped
        • You explicitly unsubscribe from a channel. The request and reply parameters contain the unsubscribe request and response PDUs, respectively.
        Specified by:
        onEnterUnsubscribed in interface SubscriptionListener
        Parameters:
        request - Unsubscribe request PDU.
        reply - Unsubscribe response PDU.

      • onLeaveUnsubscribed

        public void onLeaveUnsubscribed(UnsubscribeRequest request,
                                UnsubscribeReply reply)
        Description copied from interface: SubscriptionListener
        Called when a subscription leaves the unsubscribed state. This is the initial state for the subscription state machine.

        Subscription leaves this state when connection is established

        Specified by:
        onLeaveUnsubscribed in interface SubscriptionListener
        Parameters:
        request - Unsubscribe request PDU.
        reply - Unsubscribe response PDU.

      • onLeaveSubscribed

        public void onLeaveSubscribed(SubscribeRequest request,
                              SubscribeReply reply)
        Description copied from interface: SubscriptionListener
        Called when a subscription leaves the subscribed state.

        A subscription leaves the state when you are no longer subscribed to the channel. For example, the subscription leaves this state when the user explicitly removes the subscription from the channel or the connection drops.

      • onCreated

        public void onCreated()
        Description copied from interface: SubscriptionListener
        Called when a subscription is created.

        Note that you can create a subscription when the client is not connected to the RTM Service. The Java SDK manages the subscription workflow and sends the actual request when the client connects to the RTM Service.
